since\r
$5\r
2.6.0\r
$5\r
group\r
$7\r
generic\r
$10\r
complexity\r
$386\r
O(1) to create the new key and additional O(N*M) to reconstruct the serialized value, where N is the number of Redis objects composing the value and M their average size. For small string values the time complexity is thus O(1)+O(1*M) where M is small, so simply O(1). However for sorted set values the complexity is O(N*M*log(N)) because inserting values into sorted sets is O(log(N)).\r
